.TH "slim_xfer_msg" 9 "slim_xfer_msg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
slim_xfer_msg \- Transfer a value info message on slim device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" slim_xfer_msg
.BI "(struct slim_device *sbdev "  ","
.BI "struct slim_val_inf *msg "  ","
.BI "u8 mc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sbdev" 12
slim device to which this msg has to be transfered
.IP "msg" 12
value info message pointer
.IP "mc" 12
message code of the message
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called by drivers which want to transfer a vlaue or info elements.
.SH "RETURN"
-ETIMEDOUT: If transmission of this message timed out
